data.name: label9.ToolTip
data.value:
Select a data source using the drop-down menu to show the current value for that data source from the Exoiste platform.
Use another application or try the XMPP Commander API to write values to a data source to show up in this message window.

data.name: label11.ToolTip
data.value:
This message window tells you if the application is running or not and will also give connection problem messages.
If the application says 'Connection Problem?', check if the CIK is valid and check that you have an internet connection.

data.name: label4.ToolTip
data.value:
Each selected data box will tell the application to gather and send that data to the Exosite platform. Using Exosite Portals, you should see these data sources created and see new values reported.
Each selected box is either 1 or 2 data sources, if your data source limit is hit for your account, a warning message will show up at the bottom. Using Portals, data sources can be deleted if you no longer want them.
CPU Activity = 1 Memory Usage = 2 Battery / Power = 2 Triangle Wave = 1 Custom 'Send a Value' = 1
